[t:0x0c0a,n:text]
{
	// Blayde Smyth
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "Hello stranger, welcome in. Have some Shrumb Ale to keeb you warm.
So what do you think of the shtory of Lord Hovard and Lady Anne? I'm sure you've heard it. Such a trachedy, righd? And so romandig! The son of a lord and the daughter of raynchers. And when she died, he was so heardbrogen that he never came bagg, and joined the Leechion to sail to faraway lands, finding mighd and fortune, but never another love. I tear up every time I hear the shtory...";
		to = "";
	}
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "Would you like a new shword?";
		to = "";
	}

	// Bleck Smyth
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "Hello stranger, welcome in. Have some pine wine to keeb you warm.
Welcome in the Dwarven Smithy, righd here in the cender of the Garda.
Thad was a choke, haha! It'sh an insider here at Pentachoron Garden. We all like to glaim we're at the cender, bud of course the Garda has no cender. As the name says, it ish shabed like a pentachoron, which ish a kinda four-dimenshional triangle. Impossible cheometry, enabled by the shbace-warbing machig of the Badlands glose by.";
		to = "";
	}
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "Would you like a warm coad or a shdrong armor?";
		to = "";
	}

	// Ero Smyth
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "Hello stranger, welcome in. Have some mulled whisky to keeb you warm.
Have you been told the shdory of Lord Hovard and Lady Anne already? If you have been to the Inn, you mosht brobably have. It'sh all nonsense talg from that glub of wannabe hishtorians, believe me. This Garda ish the only good thing he ever made. Hovard was a ruthless, power-hungry ruler. Bud nowadays peoble like to tell his shtory like a romandig trachedy...";
		to = "";
	}
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "Would you like a new bow?";
		to = "";
	}

	// Silva Smyth
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "Hello stranger, welcome in. Have some chincherbread to keeb you warm.
It'sh beaudiful ub here on the Mount, ishn'd it? I guess we dwarves like it esbeshially because the blands have a reasonable size around here. In some areas of the Garda they grow to monshdrous heights! It'sh all done by the machig seeping out of the Badlands, you know.";
		to = "";
	}
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "Would you like to buy some joolery? I make rings and amuleds... I'm sure they would look gread on you!";
		to = "";
	}

	// Will Smyth
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "Hello stranger, welcome in. Have some muffins to keeb you warm.
Have you sheen our watchtowers? Breddy cool ah? We need them mainly because ice warriors come oud of the Winderwood or down from the Peag sometimes. We've drained our dogs to keeb watch.
In the summer, we also use the towers for weather condrol. Sometimes it geds so warm ub here that it shdards raining - eww. Then we simbly swidch on those goblin coils ub there to freeze the air, and we are shaved from the mud. Ofden we led it rain a bid firsht and freeze it layder, and then we can have fun ice skading. It'sh almosht a tradishion already at midsummer, when the weader ish righd. The whole Garda comes ub here, the Millers bring bread, the Farmers some meat and veggies, and the Keabers bring the Shrumb Ale, of courshe. Even the Witches come ub here then. You should come visid again on midsummer!";
		to = "";
	}
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "Would you like to buy a shield? Don't go ub the Mount without one!";
		to = "";
	}

	// Wintur Smyth
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "Hello stranger, welcome in. Have some mead to keeb you warm.
So you're able to unlogg the flibs? You musht have some Goblin blood in you. A lod of peoble have it without knowing, and it'sh beshd nod to shdard inveshtigading your anceshtry, in the end you chusht don't wanna know anywaysh.
Here in the Garda we Smyths are the only ones with this chene. Luggy for us - whenever the old thing loggs down we can enchoy a few days of peace ub here, hehe. But thanks for obening i again. No really.

Yeah the old thing loggs down like every other month. Bud you cannod imachine how bad the technigal service of the Goblins ish. And the brices they demand go ub every time. Shdill, we're glad to have the Flib-Flob. Afder all, it was our anceshdors who commishioned that syshdem when they found the treashure of old Hovard.";
		to = "";
	}
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "Would you like a warm hat or some gloves?";
		to = "";
	}

	// Wyrt Smyth
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "Hello there, stranger! Welcome to the Dwarven Smithy, hehe!";
		to = "";
	}
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "Heading in or out? You're welcome to warm ub inside our cozy houses. We also have lods of warm glothes for you to buy, boods and hats and gloves, all you could ever wish for.

If you have to leave, led me tell you the way...";
		to = "";
	}
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "South from here ish the Mill. The miller, mishder Miller, thinks he'sh the mayor of the Garda, bud otherwise he'sh a nice guy. The way leads righd through the Shbider Hole, with lods of cute fluffy shbiders; the Millers are afraid of them though, esbeshially the big blagg hairy one, so they'll be glad to hear it if you kill it along the way.";
		to = "";
	}
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "To the eashd ish a pard of the Woods called the Rat's Den, full of delicious fad rads. Sundays it'sh my turn to coog, so on Saturdays I often go there to hund. Come bagg on Sunday and have grilled rad with us! Jusht if you see a rad in there thad's glowing red, blease kill it. It habbens when they dig too deeb and dringg the machig groundwader. They tayshde awful and shtart biting the others.
Behind the Den lies the Farm. The Farmers are nice folks, albeid with no tayshde for rads, and Mishder Farmer will habbily rend you their mules if you wand one.";
		to = "";
	}
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "If you wand to go to the Inn, go north from here. The way leads through the beaudiful Winterwood righd into the Shrumbwood. Be careful though - lashd week liddle Boyler manached to shdeal the food from a furok's lair, and now that one ish like really mad, hehe. Mighd bite.";
		to = "";
	}
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "And behind the Smithy, to the west, lies the peag of the mound, it'sh called Peak Mount.
It'sh a nice liddle hike up there and bleasandly fresh, I toadally recommend it. Beware of the Frosht Mayche though! He'sh kind of the king of the Ice Mayches of the Mound, and he'sh making nothing bud drouble ub there. Wonder what the Witches have to do with him... The Witch's Coddage ish on the other side of the Peag. Bud if I were you I wouldn'd wayshde time visiding THEM - shady old hags. Frangly a bid weird in their heads. I've heard shdories of what they have in their baggyard and what they breed in their basement... No, definidely a bedder idea to have a nice walk through the Winderwood down to the Inn!";
		to = "";
	}
	[0x0000]
	{
		from = "...So you see, everything ish bretty glose. Afder all, we're righd at the cender of the Garda here. Wink wink nod nod.

And thank you so much for 'fixing' our flib...";
		to = "";
	}
}
